cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.HC 

This paper proposes a machine learning-based framework for automatic detection of Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD) using features extracted from T1-weighted MRI scans of corpus callosum and intracranial brain volume. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of conventional machine learning algorithms and deep learning architecture (VGG16), which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper deals with the detection of a medical condition, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence and Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the study involves the neuroscience domain and aims to automate the detection process, which could also make it relevant to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category.
